HEADWORD: Saltarello
<hw>Sal`ta*rel"lo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It., fr. L.
<ets>saltare</ets> to jump.]</ety> <def>A popular Italian dance in quick
3-4 or 6-8 time, running mostly in triplets, but with a hop step at the
beginning of each measure. See <er>Tarantella</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saltate</ent>⟦br⟧
